The Lion and the Mouse

One day, a lion was sleeping in the jungle. A little mouse ran over him by mistake. The lion woke up angrily and caught the mouse.

"Please let me go," said the mouse. "I may help you someday."

The lion laughed but let the mouse go.

A few days later, the lion was trapped in a hunter's net. Hearing his roar, the mouse came and gnawed the ropes with its sharp teeth. Soon, the lion was free.

The lion thanked the mouse and learned that even a small friend can be a great help.

Moral: Kindness is never wasted.

The Thirsty Crow

On a hot summer day, a crow was very thirsty. It searched everywhere for water. At last, it found a pot with a little water at the bottom.

The crow tried to drink, but its beak could not reach the water. It thought for a while and got an idea. The crow picked up small stones and dropped them into the pot one by one.

Slowly, the water level rose. When the water came near the top, the crow drank it and flew away happily.

Moral: Where there is a will, there is a way.
